The paper discusses strategies for large-scale scientific data mining of social and economic data, as well as the creation of centers for computational social science and risk analysis. This suggests that the paper may fall under the categories of social computing (cs.SI), cybernetics (cs.CY), cryptography and security (cs.CR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and systems and control (cs.SD).
